Implemented timeout for queries, as well as reading double/boolean results. Timeout works by setting a max query time for the fuseki server, then catching it in the query whenever it fails, and returning a "timeout element" that is responsible for showing the timeout. Also implemented Printing of execution time, precision, recall, entities found and % timeout. Created a set of properties so that these can be stored for each run.
Next up: Start creating some new strategies and testing the result. The baseline BFS on 100 samples had a recall of about 85%, but found on average 88423 entities and used 12s.
Aggregate feature v0.3 done. Had to create some extra queries. Also made a sample sized dataset to enable faster testing.

Aggregate feature v0.7 done. Had to create some extra queries. The strategy is working, but it is a way too slow. Have to do some tunining. Would also like to incorporate value match into the strategy.
Starting on new strategy BFS. Categorizing descriptive/ entity connecting properties is done. Next up: Expand node strategy.
